Secure GitHub Action (Backend – Spring Boot)

Artifact is created only if CodeSweep passes

name: Backend DevSecOps Pipeline

on:
  pull_request:
    branches: [ main ]
  push:
    branches: [ main ]

jobs:

  backend-scan-build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    defaults:
      run:
        working-directory: backend

    steps:

    - name: Checkout Repository
      uses: actions/checkout@v4

    # Setup Java
    - name: Setup JDK
      uses: actions/setup-java@v4
      with:
        distribution: 'temurin'
        java-version: '17'

    # Run CodeSweep Security Scan
    - name: Run HCL AppScan CodeSweep
      id: codesweep
      uses: HCL-TECH-SOFTWARE/appscan-codesweep-action@v2.1
      env:
        APPSCAN_KEY: ${{ secrets.APPSCAN_KEY }}
        APPSCAN_SECRET: ${{ secrets.APPSCAN_SECRET }}

    # Build Spring Boot Application
    - name: Build Backend
      if: success()     # Will only run if CodeSweep succeeds
      run: mvn clean package -DskipTests

    # Upload Artifact
    - name: Upload Backend Artifact
      if: success()     # Artifact only created if scan + build pass
      uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
      with:
        name: backend-jar
        path: backend/target/*.jar
Pipeline Flow
Checkout
   ↓
CodeSweep Security Scan
   ↓
IF scan passes
   ↓
Spring Boot Build
   ↓
Artifact Upload

If CodeSweep finds policy violations and fails, the pipeline stops and artifact is NOT created.

Even Better (Enterprise DevSecOps Pattern)

Separate Security Gate Job

jobs:

  security-scan:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Run CodeSweep
        uses: HCL-TECH-SOFTWARE/appscan-codesweep-action@v2.1

  build-backend:
    needs: security-scan
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    if: needs.security-scan.result == 'success'

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - run: mvn clean package
      - uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: backend-jar
          path: backend/target/*.jar

This creates a true DevSecOps security gate.

Security Scan (CodeSweep)
        ↓
      PASS
        ↓
       Build
        ↓
     Artifact

If scan fails → pipeline stops before build.

✅ This is the recommended enterprise DevSecOps gating approach.
